  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Increasing attendances by children (aged 0-16 years) at UK emergency departments (EDs) is
      putting pressure on the National Health Service (NHS). Health professionals make complex
      judgements on whether children attending EDs can be sent home safely or require admission.
      The Pennine Acute Hospitals (PAT) Paediatric Observation Priority Score (PAT-POPS) was
      developed as an ED-specific screening tool for this purpose. A preliminary study showed it to
      be a potentially effective tool for deciding admission of children from the ED. Therefore,
      the focus of this study is to refine the original screening tool.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
